# Enrich — Experience

Apply for job history from CVs, LinkedIn experience section, perf reviews, or user dictation.

Often invoked from `profile-enrich-cv.mdc`; can run standalone.

## Target file

`ai-agents/database/experience.json` → `records[]`

## Record shape

```json
{
  "id": "exp-{company-slug}-{year-start}",
  "company": "Company name",
  "role": "Title",
  "period": { "start": "2021-03", "end": "2024-06", "current": false },
  "type": "employment | contract | freelance",
  "location": "City / Remote",
  "remote": true,
  "domain": "e.g. e-commerce, SaaS",
  "teamSize": null,
  "summary": "1-2 sentences",
  "responsibilities": [],
  "projects": [{ "name": "...", "description": "...", "projectCacheId": null }],
  "technologies": [],
  "challenges": [],
  "outcomeIds": [],
  "architectureNotes": [],
  "leadership": [],
  "relatedRoles": ["backend", "devops"],
  "featured": false,
  "sourceIds": [],
  "confidence": "verified",
  "publicSafe": true,
  "enrichment_status": "complete",
  "enriched_at": "...",
  "enriched_by": "cursor"
}
```

## Steps

1. Dedupe by `company` + overlapping `period` — merge into existing record if same job.
2. Link `projectCacheId` when work maps to `projects.cache.json` entry.
3. Link `outcomeIds` for metrics stored in `outcomes.json`.
4. `featured: true` only for roles user flags or strongest 2–3 careers entries.

## Rules

- Evidence only; `confidence: "draft"` if dates or company name unclear.
- Anonymize company as `Company (NDA)` only if user requests.
- Perf review content → `leadership`, `responsibilities`; mark `publicSafe: false` if internal.
